723572f-a.text:
56-66, 68, and 72-76 (left to right) Trinity Place, at, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of Rector Street, showing the 26-story Electric Bond and Share Co. Building (No. 56-66), the 6-story Horn and Hardart Building (No. 68), and the 24-story Trinity Court Building as seen across the Rector Street station of the Sixth Ave. Elevated Line. Also shown (foreground) is a portion of Trinity Church, and grave yard extending west from Broadway to Trinity Place. On the extreme left is Rector Street west from Broadway (not seen) to and including West Street, with Pier 8 and the Hudson River partially visible. This view was taken from the New York Stock Exchange Building, at the S.W. corner of Broad and Wall Streets.
August 7, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

723571f-a.text:
(1)
Trinity Place, south from and including Rector Street, showing (right foreground) a portion of the 23-story building No. 2 Rector Street at the N.W. corner; the rear of Trinity Church (left foreground), and a portion of the 21-story Empire Building at the S.E. corner of Rector Street. Also shown (centre background) is the 32-story Whitehall Building at the N.W. corner of West Street and Battery Place, and the Statue of Liberty (Bedloe's Island) faintly discernible. Note also a portion of
the Sixth Ave. Elevated line.
August 20, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
Trinity Tlace and Broadway,showing Trinity Church and Church Yard.
